# AGENTS.md - Laravel DDD Toolkit

## Project architecture

This project uses Laravel DDD Toolkit.

The architecture is based on:

- vertical modules;
- hexagonal architecture by default;
- pragmatic tactical DDD;
- Laravel-native workflows.

## Module structure

Business capabilities live under:

```text
app/Modules/{Module}/
|-- Domain/
|-- Application/
|   `-- Ports/
|       |-- In/
|       `-- Out/
`-- Infrastructure/
```

Use `app/Modules`, not `app/Domains`.

Use `make:module`, not `make:domain`.

## Layer rules

### Domain

Domain contains:

- entities;
- value objects;
- domain events;
- domain exceptions;
- business rules.

Domain must not depend on:

- Laravel;
- Eloquent;
- HTTP;
- Jobs;
- Infrastructure;
- external SDKs.

### Application

Application contains:

- use cases;
- DTOs;
- inbound ports;
- outbound ports.

Application may depend on Domain.

Application must not depend on:

- Controllers;
- Requests;
- Eloquent models;
- Infrastructure adapters.

### Infrastructure

Infrastructure contains:

- Controllers;
- Requests;
- Eloquent models;
- persistence adapters;
- integrations;
- jobs;
- listeners;
- providers;
- Laravel-specific code.

Infrastructure may depend on Application and Domain.

## Ports and adapters

Ports live in:

```text
Application/Ports/In
Application/Ports/Out
```

Adapters live in:

```text
Infrastructure/Persistence/Adapters
Infrastructure/Integrations
```

Repositories in this architecture are usually outbound ports, not Domain contracts.

Do not create `Domain/Contracts` for the default hexagonal structure.

## Commands

Prefer these commands:

```bash
php artisan make:module Order
php artisan make:port Order OrderRepository --type=out
php artisan make:adapter Order EloquentOrderRepository --port=OrderRepository --type=persistence
php artisan make:integration Payment Stripe
php artisan ddd:check
```

Do not reintroduce `make:domain`.

## Pragmatism

Do not force CQRS, Event Sourcing or repositories everywhere.

Eloquent is allowed in Infrastructure.

Repositories are optional and should only be generated when they add value.

Laravel conventions should be preserved whenever possible.

## Architectural checks

Before finishing changes that affect modules, layers, namespaces or generated code, run:

```bash
php artisan ddd:check
```

## Module-level AI docs

New modules may include their own `README.md` and `AGENTS.md`.

Module-level `AGENTS.md` files provide more specific instructions for that module and should be respected over generic project-level guidance when editing files inside the module.
